cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with compressed sensing and matrix completion, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, the focus on handling corrupted data suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Gaussian sensing matrices and \ell1 minimization in Theorem 1 further supports the likelihood of cs.IT. The mention of low-rank matrix recovery in Theorem 3 suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category. The use of optimization methods in all three theorems suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of corrupted samples suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category, as this is a common problem in network data analysis.
